# Normalize line endings to LF in both the index AND the working tree.
#
# Previous policy: forced CRLF for *.cs / *.csproj / *.yml / etc. That worked
# when the repo was Windows-only, but it breaks the moment Linux tooling
# enters the picture: Jenkins agents (Linux), Dependabot (Linux), GitHub
# Actions runners (often Linux), and any *nix editor write LF, which then
# disagrees with the `eol=crlf` attribute on every checkout. Result: every
# Dependabot PR shows whole-file diffs as line-ending churn, and Jenkins's
# pre-merge step refuses to merge `main` into a PR branch because the
# working tree comes out "dirty" on every fresh checkout.
#
# This policy pins LF for all text files. Windows editors handle LF fine
# (Visual Studio / VS Code / Rider all preserve existing line endings;
# `core.autocrlf=true` no longer fights with the attribute either).
# `text=auto` auto-detects binary vs text via content inspection so we
# don't have to enumerate every binary type. Per-extension entries are
# belt-and-suspenders and serve as documentation for "yes, this is text".

* text=auto eol=lf

# Source code
*.cs           text eol=lf
*.csproj       text eol=lf
*.sln          text eol=lf
*.props        text eol=lf
*.targets      text eol=lf
*.razor        text eol=lf
*.cshtml       text eol=lf
*.css          text eol=lf
*.js           text eol=lf
*.ts           text eol=lf

# Scripts
*.sh           text eol=lf
*.ps1          text eol=lf

# CI / config
*.yml          text eol=lf
*.yaml         text eol=lf
*.json         text eol=lf
*.toml         text eol=lf
*.config       text eol=lf
*.xml          text eol=lf

# Docs
*.md           text eol=lf
*.txt          text eol=lf

# Editor / VCS metadata
*.editorconfig text eol=lf
.gitattributes text eol=lf
.gitignore     text eol=lf

# Container / infra
Dockerfile     text eol=lf
*.dockerfile   text eol=lf
*.conf         text eol=lf

# Explicit binary markers (also auto-detected, listed for clarity)
*.dll          binary
*.exe          binary
*.nupkg        binary
*.png          binary
*.jpg          binary
*.jpeg         binary
*.gif          binary
*.ico          binary
*.snk          binary
*.pfx          binary
